Text.string: Yo, Lilith. The Vault Hunter's back!
Vault Hunter, did you bring me that lock of Typhon's hair? Right, yes... inappropriate timing. End of the universe and all.||—Just put it in my lab.
I'm sorry, starlight.
Hnnrghhhhhaaaagh!
I'm with ya, Vault Hunter!
Typhon...
You gotta stop her... it's too late for me. Just promise me something. Don't... be... the last Vault Hunters.
We won't.
He's gone...
Pandora's gonna be ripped apart. And if Tyreen leeches the Destroyer, that'll be the least of our problems. We have to stop her.

The Machine has already worked once before, sealing the Destroyer away inside Pandora millennia ago. If Tyreen leeches it, she may finally become a so-called god. Then again, what is a god but the most powerful being in the universe? Either this works, or we are all obliterated.
Vault Hunter, you are non-stop! Jacked! If I had a body, you can bet your ass I'd be a Vault Hunter, too. You know BALEX is a natural-born hunter, baby.
Cool place.
This place... I feel a connection with something... very old.
What wonders await us here?
This place could use some furniture. A nice divan.
End of the road, superfan! For you, anyway.
(sustained light efforts)
(thrown back react)
(thrown back react)
(thrown back react)
(grab effort)
(react to being grabbed)
(choke release react)
You should go down there, Tannis. I don't know who else could get this thing working.
(fall effort)
Hrgh!
(wobble)
(land react)
(getting up)
(smirk react)
Really? And work side-by-side with Typhon DeLeon? If I must, Lilith. If I must.
You got this, Tannis. And I am totally not gonna snoop around your lab for Eridian stuff while you're gone.
That's a relief.
Get geared up, Vault Hunter. Then meet Typhon at the Machine. Before it's too late.
Tannis will meet you at the entrance to the Machine. Stay on guard, killer. We don't know where Tyreen is, and she could still send COV at us at any moment. Be ready for a fight.
Ah, I see. Now those connections between the Vaults make sense. The Vaults on Promethea and Eden-6 must be the power sources for this Machine. Intriguing.
Wow, you're smart!
Good job getting that Key, killer. Give it to Tannis so she can charge it.
Bit of an understatement, don't you think?
Ha! And you know who you are. That's a rare thing in this universe.
Vault Hunter! Time to see what this Machine can do! Go ahead, put in the last Vault Key.
Oh my...
Well, let's get to it. We got a universe to save!
A dream come true... but we must focus. The first step is to locate the Machine's control console.
Them Eridians never did anything small, did they? Though I guess you do need a planet-sized machine to seal up an entire planet!
Ava... would you like to join me?
Hey, you're glowing!
Oh, you're too kind.
No, seriously!
Fascinating. Perhaps Sirens had some hand in constructing this Machine!
You know what? You remind me of Leda.
Catch me, Vault Hunter. I swoon!
If only I had a decade to study this machine. Its design is mind-gasmingly complex, but I do believe its primary operation to be fairly straightforward. To start, I require the Pandora Vault Key.
Interesting. Now, it seems we must offer the remaining Keys to the guardian statues. Then the Machine will draw power from the Vaults on those planets, closing Pandora.
To the other statues, Vault Hunter. Quickly now.
How does it work?
This way! Next up, Promethea...
Heh—good thing I never told my daughter about this place. But stay sharp. If I know the Eridians, there's sure to be some Guardians around here.
Guardians! Let's take 'em out together!
Hey, that looks like one of the statues your scientist was talkin' about. Give it the Key. Like an offering.
The Promethea Vault has been activated!
This way, Vault Hunter! Next stop, Eden-6. “Paradise” my hairy ass! But it does have its charms. Went skinny dipping in a saurian tar pit once. I was hairless for a month!
Huh, this glyph says... to reveal... the steps. Guess it means use that switch.
Whoa! Quite a schlep. Guess them Eridians didn't mind a little exercise, huh? Good thing I've got the whip! See ya up top!
This way, come on!
What the hell is this?
It's... a feeling. Here.
Cool trick, huh, Dad? Say hello to my new family!
Come on, she knows we're here. We gotta hurry!
Go on, give it the Key, like the last one!
The Machine nearly has enough power to seal Pandora! Keep going!
Last one, Vault Hunter. This way. Stay sharp.
Tyreen! You don't know what you're doing, starlight. The Destroyer's called that for a reason. It literally eats stars!
Not if I eat it first.
“Solitude is no virtue”... huh...
Guess they mean to use both switches together. Old school classic! Right, end of the world. I'll focus.
Not bad! The Nekrotafeyo statue's close. We gotta hurry!
Woah! Gross, do you taste olives?
The Nekrotafeyo statue! Oh boy... once you offer the key, better hold onto your keister!
Told ya!
All of the connections to the Vaults are activated! Return to me, fair Typhon! Vault Hunter, you may... come too.
Lilith, you might want to come down and see this.
On our way.
Tannis!
Whoa...
Tannis, is it... working?
The Vaults are all connected, but it hasn't activated yet. Pandora is still opening.
Maybe it needs a Siren's touch.
Huh. I always thought fried pickles.
Ah! Then touch it I shall! As the nihilist said on his deathbed, “here goes nothing”!
I understand now.
Holy baloney... would ya look at that!
Tannis, you all right?
Yes! So much power... and I am the conduit!
Pandora's closing!
All right! It's working!
Yeah... I'm gonna have to put a stop to that.
COV, incoming! Ava, keep them off Tannis!
On it!
It worked! Here, Vault Hunter. All yours.
This is it. You know what to do, killer.
When Troy and I were kids, we'd stare up at the night sky and dream of becoming stars. The brightest in the galaxy, Troy always said.
Starlight! Don't do this!
So we left this place behind. Went to Pandora to become Vault Hunters ourselves. We'd open the Vault of Vaults and become the biggest stars in the galaxy.
Tyreen, listen to me! This won't end the way you think it will! Trust me!
They seem so small now, our dreams. Not befitting a god. Now I'm gonna devour every last star in the universe, one by one. Until nothing shines... but me.
Almost... done...
She's here.
Hang on, Ava!
S'up?
So, how do we know this Machine thing is gonna do what it's supposed to, and not, like, blow up the whole universe?
This for me?
Haven't we done this before, Lil? I'm over it.
Hiya, starlight.
Let me go!
Nuh uh. I let you go once, and see how that turned out?
You scared old man! This is your fault! You kept us here, when the universe should have been ours!
I gave you what I could.
In order to access the Eridian machine, I'll need to charge that key. Bring it up to Sanctuary.
You're not gonna stop me from getting to the Destroyer.
I don't care! I'm gonna take what's mine!
